### KHA*ND*A 4.

1 <span id="fr_135"></span>[1](#fn_134.md). 'Under my will I take thy
heart; my mind shall thy mind follow; in my word thou shalt rejoice with
all thy heart; may B*ri*haspati join thee to me.'

2 <span id="fr_136"></span>[2](#fn_135.md). 'Thou art the Brahma*k*ârin of
Kâma, N.N.!'

3 <span id="fr_137"></span>[3](#fn_136.md). With the same text (see chap.
3, 2) he turns round as before,

4\. And touching with the span of his right hand (the student's) right
shoulder, he murmurs:

<span id="page_66">p. 66</span>

5 <span id="fr_138"></span>[5](#fn_137.md). 'A student art thou. Put on
fuel. Eat water. Do the service. Do not sleep in the day-time. Keep
silence till the putting on of fuel.'

6\. With (the words), 'Thine, Agni, is this piece of wood,' he puts the
fuel on (the fire), or silently.

